commit.message:
Major HTTP refactor

Changed HTTP handling to use a requests adapter versus the session.
This enables both HTTPClient and HTTPie integration to use the same
code.

In addition, Google OAuth is now handled by google-auth over
the deprecated oauth2client.

commit.message:
Added an HTTPie transport plugin

The new contrib plugin enables the direct use of pykube as the transport
layer for HTTPie.

For example:

	pip install httpie pykube
	http pykube://minikube

The above example will enable HTTPie send an HTTP request to the kubeconfig
context named minikube (dealing with certificates and authentication for you).

This isn't 100% compatible with pykube credential handling yet. Further refactoring
is needed to support Google OAuth.

commit.message: Fixes typo in README

Test if selector is instance of six.string_types

In python2 it's possible to pass a `unicode` string as a selector, which doesn't trigger this condition, causing an error. By using `six.string_types` instead of `str` we make sure to test for both kinds of strings.

Add ready property to replication controller class

This method is available on both pods and deployments. No reason we can't have it on RC's as well. I've currently got this method monkey patched on to `pykube.ReplicationController` in my project. Seems to be working well.
Bumped to 0.15.0
